ypeDoc = await db.collection('carSeatTypes').doc(carSeatType).get(); const carModelInfo = carModelDoc.data(); const carSeatTypeInfo = carSeatTypeDoc.data(); // Generate the guide const guide = \` # Car Seat Installation Guide for {motherName} Dear {motherName}, thank you for choosing to prioritize your child's safety on the road. Installing a car seat can seem daunting, but with this guide, you'll be able to do it confidently and correctly. Please follow these steps carefully to ensure a safe and secure installation. Preparation Before you start, make sure you have all the necessary tools and read the car seat manual carefully. You can find a sample manual for your {carSeatType} car seat [here]({carSeatTypeInfo.manualUrl}). Take a few minutes to review the manual and familiarize yourself with the installation process. Installation To install the car seat, follow these steps: 1. Locate the car seat mounting points in your {carModel} vehicle. Refer to your vehicle's manual (page {carModelInfo.manualPage}) for more information. 2. Place the car seat in the vehicle and attach it to the mounting points using the provided hardware. 3. Tighten the harness according to the manufacturer's instructions. **Warning:** Common mistakes to avoid include not tightening the harness enough or not securing the car seat to the vehicle correctly. To see a video tutorial specific to your {carModel} vehicle, click [here]({carModelInfo.videoTutorialUrl}). Additional Tips elm To ensure a secure installation, make sure to: * Tighten the harness until it's snug against your child's body. * Check the car seat's level indicator to ensure it's installed correctly. * Refer to your vehicle's manual for any specific installation requirements. By following these steps and tips, you'll be able to install your car seat with confidence and keep your child safe on the road. \`; return guide; } module.exports = generateGuide; \`\`\` I hope this implementation meets the requirements. Let me review the cod